llowing{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2011-06-05T21:37:21Z","updated_at":"2011-06-05T21:37:21Z","body":"On the example itself makes sense.\n\nI just tried the following:\n\n``` ruby\ndescribe \"something\" do\n  it \"should pass\" do\n    1.should == 1\n  end\n\n  it \"should fail\" do\n    1.should == 2\n  end\n\n  after(:each) do\n    puts \"FAILED!!!\" if example.execution_result[:status] == 'failed'\n  end\nend\n```\n\n...but I didn't see the \"FAILED!!!\" that I was expecting to see in the output. Here's what I got:\n\n```\nnat$ rspec thing2.rb \n.F\n\nFailures:\n\n  1) something should fail\n     Failure/Error: 1.should == 2\n       expected: 2\n            got: 1 (using ==)\n     # ./thing2.rb:7:in `block (2 levels) in <top (required)>'\n\nFinished in 0.00103 seconds\n2 examples, 1 failure\n```\n\nWhat am I missing?\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/comments/1306064/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"natritmeyer","id":217265,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxNzI2NQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/217265?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer","html_url":"https://github.com/natritmeyer","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/natritmeyer/followe